##Because of the quarantine, the husband who never does housework has finally moved..

Micro-signal Jianjiaobuluo

Function description, pepper tribe, amplify your voice! Chinese Women Workers Exclusive Information Platform, you are welcome to pay attention!

ABSTRACT: "others feel bored at home, but I have a very full life. "

When did the outbreak end, when did the boss inform the workers, and when did the children go to school -- Foshan -- became the most vexing and disturbing question for most people since the outbreak of the epidemic.
For many people, the days of isolation at home are long and boring. But for some women who have been "family caregivers" for a long time, the special circumstances of the epidemic have unexpectedly freed them from the heavy housework. Facing all kinds of accidents and difficulties brought by the epidemic, they also give full play to their life wisdom, one by one.
Here's their story.

SIFAN:
Neither of them could go to work, and the husband finally started cooking.
As far as I'm concerned, the effect of the epidemic is that there's no money to be made. I haven't been paid in two months, and the school is pressing for the child's tuition. In late February, my boss informed me that I could start work at the beginning of March. But when I returned from Hunan, I was told I would have to work later, so I stayed home.
I can't go to work. Two kids can't go to school. Now, they can only use the mobile phone to surf the Internet class. Fortunately, they just review the previous taught knowledge, or learn some interesting knowledge, has not been formally into the next semester's curriculum, so parents will not be particularly hard.
As a parent, all I have to do is remind them that it's time for class, or help them take pictures and videos of their homework. After all, it is a cell phone class, I am not very comfortable, worried about their lack of self-awareness, such as whether they will listen to the class when playing games, so occasionally or to supervise.
However, I am also worried about the children's eyesight as they look at their mobile phones all day long. Although each class, the children will have a ten-minute break, the teacher will remind them to do eye exercises, but I still feel that this is not convenient. Apart from the eyesight problem, I don't know if the children really understand this teaching method. After all, not face to face, they have problems, and can not timely feedback to teachers.

At 9:00 a.m. , the kids start their online classes
(photo provided for interviewees)
To be honest, being at home for so long, I find it really depressing. Back in Shenzhen, we rarely go out, occasionally my husband will scan code out to the supermarket to buy some food. All I do is get up, eat, do the chores, take care of the kids, and one day is over, and the next day it's over.
When I wasn't at work, I did all the housework myself. When I started working, the baby's grandmother came over to help. After the outbreak, my husband and I have no class, I let my husband do housework, and said to him: "I eat lying down sleep, I do not work. " These two days he began to cook. After all, neither of us are working now, and the housework is still negotiable, and he wouldn't do it if asked to.
Every day now, our lives revolve around Seven necessities.

SIFAN's husband is preparing lunch

After dinner, Sifan is responsible for washing the dishes

Sister Fang:
I couldn't get a mask, so I made one at home.
In mid January, I saw the news on my mobile phone that there was an outbreak in Wuhan. But I did not pay much attention to it at that time. I felt that only one place appeared, and the others should be fine. So I bought a ticket and went back to Huizhou for the New Year.
When I got back to Huizhou, there was more and more information, and I realized it was really serious, so I decided to buy a face mask. But a lot of masks have been looted, I saw online some shops can buy, but not sure when can be shipped, and so do not know when, finally had to cancel the order.
After that, I called my family, warned them to be careful, and asked them to buy me a mask. However, when I actually bought the mask, I found that it was inferior product, so I had to make do. Thankfully, some of my sisters found out about me and helped me get a real mask, and I'm really grateful to them.

Sister Fang
But my family back home is clearly having a harder time than I ever had with a face mask. As I am from Hubei, most of my relatives are also in the hard hit areas.
After calling relatives, they admitted that the situation was still serious: they themselves were afraid to go out to avoid getting sick after the infection, so they had to stay at home every day and were very depressed emotionally. I'm sorry to hear that, but there's nothing I can do about it. I just hope it passes soon.
Now, I am in Shenzhen to help my daughter with two children, the older is seven years old, the younger is just over a year old. However, now the son-in-law has not returned to work, wages do not know when to pay; the older children to school, and school fees; coupled with this year in January and raised the rent, but also to pay the mortgage. So our family, as is the epidemic came, the pressure of life is also big, can only save.
But it's a lot easier to shop here. Because in Huizhou, we were sent home with no choice but to come here, get our passes and go to the market. Later, my daughter also told me that during the Chinese New Year, food prices were very expensive, and then was reported, so now it is cheap again, as before the epidemic, we can ease some of the pressure on family expenses.
Before the outbreak, my daughter and son-in-law had to work, and I had to do the shopping, the cooking, the cooking. If they get off work early, they help. During this period, they can not return to work, so the housework do not need me to do, they also told me to rest more.
Can Not go out of the day, I watch the news every day, occasionally chat with friends, have a good life.

Fang made breakfast for the whole family

The little granddaughter wants to look out the window

When she couldn't buy a mask, Fang made a homemade mask out of gauze and plastic wrap

Kapok:
People think it's boring at home, but I live a full life.
When I first learned about the outbreak, it was January 19th, and then on New Year's Eve, I started to feel really, really bad.
With more and more information about the online epidemic, the supermarket where I work is in short supply. Customers are rushing to buy, most of them are stocking up on oil and rice. Usually we sell things, sell out for a period of time, so do not rush replenishment; now is a sale, two hours will be gone, a day to increase at least two or three times.

Kapok usually work in the supermarket, during the outbreak of business as usual
In the meantime, we're being asked to wear masks. At the beginning of work, I saw colleagues wear some do not wear, so it may not be too severe, I do not particularly want to wear. But then, the company issued a mask, definitely must wear, but also gave us a special meeting, said the supermarket customers are many and not fixed, remind us must protect themselves.
Slowly, I began to feel a sense of panic myself. Because when I went to buy more masks, the pharmacy was almost sold out; then I went to buy disinfectant, which was also sold out. Even if later know some purchase channels, I went to ask the mask price, rise is really too high, a thirty yuan, I really can not afford Ah!
So I had to wear a mask at work and wash my hands after work. When I get home from work, I change my clothes, sterilize my phone with alcohol, and clean my house. I'm GonNa have to do everything I can to avoid an outbreak.
However, I read in the news that individual immunity and resistance are very important. So I began to go to bed early, do not stay up late, early to bed and early to rise. I would like to lead a regular life some, may be a good physique, strong resistance, it is the best personal efforts to fight the epidemic. If it's still contagious, I'll just let it happen. Fear doesn't help.
Later, I saw more and more information about the outbreak on the Internet. I've seen enough, and I really think that people who aren't sick will freak out. So in free time, I began to do some of their favorite food, such as steamed bread, steamed buns, dumplings and so on, and try to live a good life.

The usual holiday when the steamed bread, steamed buns, dumplings, Pan steaming, can be eaten as breakfast, economical and affordable
During the outbreak, many people were bored at home and couldn't get out of the house. But I'm different, and I feel like I'm running out of time. I used to get up at 5 am to make breakfast, do housework after work, and watch my children go to bed early in the evening. Years ago, my husband went home with the children. I stayed here alone, so I had a lot of extra time.
Now I have a lot of things to learn, such as through reading, You can learn more knowledge, or just relax, watch TV. I signed up for driver's ED years ago. My husband said: "You test a driver's license, then we can earn money, can buy a car. " I think anyway the age is getting older, do not learn the words have no chance. Learning makes people feel more fulfilled, so I'll put everything else on hold for now.
After all, a man needs something to live for. This is how I spend my days.

Kapok's little desk where she reads and writes

Azalea on the windowsill
